SIMPLE: biffin
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Biffin
<hw>Bif"fin</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Beaufin</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sort of apple peculiar to
Norfolk, Eng.</def> <note>[Sometimes called <xex>beaufin</xex>; but
properly <xex>beefin</xex> (it is said), from its resemblance to raw
beef.]</note> <rj><au>Wright.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A baked apple pressed down into a flat, round cake;
a dried apple.</def> <rj><au>Dickens.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bifid</ent>⟦br⟧
